52.4	David_D._Friedman	David D. Friedman	David Director Friedman (born February 12, 1945) is an American economist, author, and libertarian theorist. He is known as a leader in anarcho-capitalist political theory, which is the subject of his most popular book, The Machinery of Freedom (1973, revised 1989). He has authored others, including Price Theory: An Intermediate Text (1986), Law's Order: What Economics Has to Do with Law and Why It Matters (2000), Hidden Order: The Economics of Everyday Life (1996), and Future Imperfect (2008).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/14/DavidFriedmanOwnPhoto.jpg/220px-DavidFriedmanOwnPhoto.jpg
